[1]
Date: Tue 12 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The China Daily online, Tue 12 Dec 2006 [edited]
<http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2006-12/12/content_756279.htm>

Rabies heads fatal disease list again in November
-------------------------------------------------
Rabies killed more people in China than any other infectious disease for
the 6th consecutive month in November [2006], the Ministry of Health said
yesterday [11 Dec 2006]. There were 270 deaths caused by rabies last month
[November 2006] out of 743 deaths due to infectious disease on the Chinese
mainland, according to the Ministry of Health. In all, 354 people were
reportedly bitten by rabid animals, the Ministry said.
Rabies has topped the list of the most deadly infectious disease since June
2006; before that, tuberculosis was number one. In November 2006,
tuberculosis was the 2nd-ranked killer, followed by AIDS and hepatitis B,
Ministry figures showed.
China ranks 2nd in the world after India in the number of reported cases of
[human] rabies, sources said. Every year, more than 50 000 people around
the world die of the disease, most of them from developing countries.
[byline: By Liu Li]
